Members of the Assembly of Wales do not want to "go to the mappets"
Among some members of the National Assembly, there is dissatisfaction with the proposal to adopt the abbreviation MWP (Member of the Welsh Parliament – Member of Parliament of Wales) for their names.
The problematic solution relates to plans to change the name of the Assembly to the Parliament of Wales.
Members of the Assembly from different political parties are concerned about the possible jokes with this abbreviation.
One Labour member, expressing his party’s opinion, expressed concern that the new abbreviation “refutes Twp and Pwp”.
For our readers not from Wales: in Welsh twp means "stupid", and pwp - "duck".
According to a member of the Assembly from the Wales Party, his organization as a whole was “dissatisfied” and offered other options.
Representatives of the conservative party “do not object” to the new abbreviation, but note that MWP is close by writing to the word Muppet (mappet).
In this context, the letter w in Welsh is pronounced roughly like the letter u in Yorkshire English.
The Committee of the Assembly, currently drafting a bill to change the name, made the following statement: “The final decision on the name of the Members of the Assembly will, of course, remain with them.”
Under the Wales Governance Act of 2017, the National Assembly of Wales is authorized to change its name.
In June, the Committee published the results of a public opinion poll on the proposed options, according to which the option of “Welsh Parliament” instead of “Assembly” found broad support among the local population.
As for the names of the members of the Assembly, the Committee preferred the Welsh Parliament Members (WMP) option, while the MWP option received the greatest public support.
It seems that the members of the Assembly are proposing other options, but it will not be easy for the Chairman, Elina Jones, to find a solution that fits all. We will remind you that the draft law on amendments should be submitted in a few weeks.
Reform laws will include other modifications to the Assembly ' s working process, including new rules on disqualification of members of the Assembly and the structure of the Committee ' s system.
The members of the Assembly will vote in favour of the final version of their name during the debate on the draft law.
