Many Bolivians will be watching the decision-making process in the International Court of Justice on big screens across the country, hoping that the tribunal in The Hague will be able to support Bolivia's statement that, after decades of tense negotiations, Chile has an obligation to negotiate Bolivia's sovereign entry to the sea.
